1
00:00:11,541 --> 00:00:14,791
Oh, crap. Time's almost up.
We've got 60 seconds!

2
00:00:14,875 --> 00:00:16,875
We're almost there!
Go, go!

3
00:00:17,875 --> 00:00:19,416
So close,

4
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:22,916
but this game won't end
till the only one left is me.

5
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,541
You're in our way!

6
00:00:26,666 --> 00:00:28,250
[NATSUKO]
This ends here.

7
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:31,708
[NOBUAKI] I don't have the time
to deal with you, Natsuko.

8
00:00:31,791 --> 00:00:33,208
[screams]

9
00:00:33,291 --> 00:00:35,708
-Are you okay?
-Nobuaki!

10
00:00:35,791 --> 00:00:38,041
Don't wait!
Keep going! Hurry!

11
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,416
[grunts]

12
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:45,708
[gasps]

13
00:00:45,791 --> 00:00:48,750
[giggling]

14
00:02:22,875 --> 00:02:27,333
After this, I'm gonna get
strong, like they are.

15
00:02:27,416 --> 00:02:29,916
Teru and Nobuaki
will be proud of me.

16
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:33,000
What? You're running just so
other people will be impressed?

17
00:02:35,250 --> 00:02:38,625
You gotta be strong now.
Don't wait for later, you idiot.

18
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:42,291
And do it for yourself,
not for anyone else.

19
00:02:43,250 --> 00:02:44,541
Right.

20
00:02:54,625 --> 00:02:56,000
[RYOU]
This is it.

21
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:00,000
[phone chimes]

22
00:03:03,416 --> 00:03:05,166
A message from the King.

23
00:03:05,250 --> 00:03:07,375
I kind of can't believe
we made it.

24
00:03:07,458 --> 00:03:10,250
Nobuaki. We have to help him.

25
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:12,083
[NOBUAKI]
No need for that.

26
00:03:12,166 --> 00:03:13,625
I'm right here.

27
00:03:13,708 --> 00:03:15,750
RIONA:
Oh, thank God.

28
00:03:16,875 --> 00:03:18,541
What about the rest?

29
00:03:18,625 --> 00:03:20,958
They should've gotten
here way before us.

30
00:03:21,958 --> 00:03:24,750
You know, I'm pretty sure
you can put Aya down now.

31
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:27,958
Unless you plan on carrying her
for the rest of the night.

32
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:30,708
Oh, right.

33
00:03:33,208 --> 00:03:34,708
Ryou.

34
00:03:34,791 --> 00:03:36,375
Will you check to see
how many messages

35
00:03:36,458 --> 00:03:39,125
we got from the King confirming
who made it to the summit?

36
00:03:39,208 --> 00:03:41,083
Yeah, sure, let's see.

37
00:03:41,166 --> 00:03:42,625
Only five.

38
00:03:42,708 --> 00:03:44,958
The four of us and Natsuko.

39
00:03:45,041 --> 00:03:48,416
So, no others made it.

40
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,416
-[chimes]
-Huh?

41
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:52,416
[gasping]

42
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:54,458
Look. It's them.

43
00:03:56,458 --> 00:03:59,166
I don't get it. They were all
so far ahead of us.

44
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:01,875
Something bad must've happened
to them along the way.

45
00:04:01,958 --> 00:04:04,041
[footsteps approach]

46
00:04:04,125 --> 00:04:06,166
Are you behind this,
too, Natsuko?

47
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:08,541
Tell me!

48
00:04:08,625 --> 00:04:10,500
Aren't you getting
a little tired of blaming me

49
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:12,250
for other people's mistakes yet?

50
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:13,833
[spits]

51
00:04:13,916 --> 00:04:15,583
By the way,

52
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:18,875
not a bad kick,
I can still feel it.

53
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:21,541
Did you see Takuya and the girls
anywhere on the trails?

54
00:04:21,625 --> 00:04:24,208
Oh, yes.
Our paths crossed.

55
00:04:24,291 --> 00:04:27,791
Unfortunately, all three of them
seemed very disoriented.

56
00:04:27,875 --> 00:04:30,208
I wouldn't be surprised
if they got lost.

57
00:04:30,291 --> 00:04:33,041
It's easy to get hurt out here.

58
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:39,125
[groans]

59
00:04:39,208 --> 00:04:42,250
[NATSUKO] Losers.
And they were so close.

60
00:04:47,875 --> 00:04:49,125
Now, then,

61
00:04:49,208 --> 00:04:51,666
I wonder what
our next order will be.

62
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:53,958
Maybe it'll be the final one.

63
00:04:54,041 --> 00:04:56,500
The end.
Who do you think'll win?

64
00:04:56,583 --> 00:04:59,541
-No one wins, you monster.
-[thuds]

65
00:04:59,625 --> 00:05:01,166
[grunts]

66
00:05:03,041 --> 00:05:05,666
[RIONA]
Nobuaki!

67
00:05:05,750 --> 00:05:08,750
Ryou, have you lost
your damn mind?

68
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:10,041
[rock thuds]

69
00:05:10,125 --> 00:05:12,791
I'm going to get stronger.

70
00:05:12,875 --> 00:05:16,125
I can protect other people,
just like they always tried to.

71
00:05:16,208 --> 00:05:18,458
[RIONA]
What are you talking about?

72
00:05:18,541 --> 00:05:22,666
We got a new order.
We have to make a human doll.

73
00:05:22,750 --> 00:05:24,666
To do that, we have to cut
our own bodies into pieces

74
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:26,583
and put them together.

75
00:05:26,666 --> 00:05:29,541
We need a head, torso,
two arms, and two legs.

76
00:05:29,625 --> 00:05:32,708
They can all be from the same
person or some from each of us.

77
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:36,500
The thing is,
we have to cut ourselves.

78
00:05:36,583 --> 00:05:39,625
No. There's no way
we can do that.

79
00:05:39,708 --> 00:05:42,041
We've had some pretty sick
commands in the last few days,

80
00:05:42,125 --> 00:05:44,458
but this is beyond disgusting.

81
00:05:44,541 --> 00:05:47,750
We're just high school students.
We're real people!

82
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,916
Not just body parts
to play with!

83
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:52,541
What, are we supposed
to glue the parts together?

84
00:05:52,625 --> 00:05:56,083
He's treating us like we're
a bunch of serial killers.

85
00:05:56,166 --> 00:05:57,750
No need to worry.

86
00:05:57,833 --> 00:06:01,250
I'll cut off all my limbs
so you guys don't have to.

87
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:05,625
I'll die. The only problem is,
I can't cut off my own head.

88
00:06:05,708 --> 00:06:07,416
You think that's the problem?

89
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:10,166
Are you even listening
to how crazy you sound?

90
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:12,208
You said you wanted
to become stronger.

91
00:06:12,291 --> 00:06:14,333
But this is suicide!

92
00:06:14,416 --> 00:06:18,208
No. I'm sacrificing myself
for my friends.

93
00:06:18,291 --> 00:06:19,375
[gasps]

94
00:06:21,458 --> 00:06:24,791
Here you go. Now, my advice
would be to do it fast

95
00:06:24,875 --> 00:06:26,791
before the shock wears off.

96
00:06:27,791 --> 00:06:30,583
This is perfect, seriously.

97
00:06:30,666 --> 00:06:33,541
This entire time, I've been
wanting to help everyone else.

98
00:06:33,625 --> 00:06:36,375
Just like Teru helped Nobuaki.

99
00:06:38,083 --> 00:06:40,791
-Ryou, no!
-I can protect all of you.

100
00:06:40,875 --> 00:06:42,833
[saw rumbling]

101
00:06:42,916 --> 00:06:44,791
[rumbling stops]

102
00:06:44,875 --> 00:06:47,583
-Put it down.
-Stay back!

103
00:06:47,666 --> 00:06:50,041
Someone has to be dismembered.

104
00:06:50,125 --> 00:06:53,083
We both know that.
[RYOU gasps]

105
00:06:53,166 --> 00:06:54,791
[NATSUKO]
Okay, Ryou.

106
00:06:54,875 --> 00:06:56,375
Pull the starter again, hard.

107
00:06:56,458 --> 00:06:59,750
And this time,
hold down the button. Got it?

108
00:07:02,333 --> 00:07:04,541
I'm going to become a real man!

109
00:07:04,625 --> 00:07:06,916
-[saw buzzing]
-No matter what it takes!

110
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:10,041
[screaming]

111
00:07:10,125 --> 00:07:11,750
Yeah, that's the way, Ryou!

112
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:14,125
-Keep going!
-Stop him, please!

113
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:17,750
Oh, no, looks like
it's stuck on your bone.

114
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:20,333
No problem.

115
00:07:20,416 --> 00:07:22,083
[screaming]

116
00:07:22,166 --> 00:07:24,291
I'm here to help
a friend in need.

117
00:07:24,375 --> 00:07:29,041
[screaming]

118
00:07:29,125 --> 00:07:31,000
-[leg thuds]
-[RYOU whimpers]

119
00:07:33,458 --> 00:07:37,166
[NATSUKO] That's one, Ryou.
But you've got three more to go.

120
00:07:37,250 --> 00:07:40,625
If you're not careful, you'll
bleed out before you finish up.

121
00:07:40,708 --> 00:07:44,833
Oh, dear.
You're already dead?

122
00:07:44,916 --> 00:07:46,875
♪

123
00:07:46,958 --> 00:07:48,416
[RIONA sobs]

124
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:52,333
I can't.
This is too horrible.

125
00:07:52,416 --> 00:07:54,375
[saw rumbling]

126
00:07:54,458 --> 00:07:57,541
-[gasps]
-So, what should we do next?

127
00:07:57,625 --> 00:08:01,125
Would it be rude to wake Aya
and Nobuaki with this chain saw?

128
00:08:01,208 --> 00:08:05,541
You... you aren't even human.
You're some kind of demon!

129
00:08:05,625 --> 00:08:07,875
I won't let you hurt any of us.

130
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:11,125
[scoffs] Look at you,
cowering on the ground.

131
00:08:11,208 --> 00:08:12,958
What do you think
you're going to do?

132
00:08:14,958 --> 00:08:17,958
[MATSUOKA] You killed Ryou,
didn't you? Didn't you?

133
00:08:18,958 --> 00:08:21,125
You'll pay for this!

134
00:08:21,208 --> 00:08:25,375
Bring him back!
Ryou was too good to die!

135
00:08:25,458 --> 00:08:28,166
Shut up.
And stay outta my way!

136
00:08:28,250 --> 00:08:30,291
[chain saw buzzing]

137
00:08:32,916 --> 00:08:34,416
Well, that's great.

138
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:35,958
Looks like Aya's
down for the count

139
00:08:36,041 --> 00:08:37,958
and we'll have to do
the work for her.

140
00:08:38,041 --> 00:08:41,750
-No. Don't.
-Where should we cut first?

141
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:46,208
Stop this. Please, someone help.
I can't take it.

142
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:47,875
[scoffs]

143
00:08:47,958 --> 00:08:50,583
You always acted like you were
so high and mighty in class.

144
00:08:50,666 --> 00:08:52,250
"Someone help me!"

145
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:55,250
"I can't take it!"
It's adorable.

146
00:08:55,333 --> 00:08:57,541
"Helpless" is
a good look for you.

147
00:08:57,625 --> 00:08:59,625
There's only one problem.

148
00:08:59,708 --> 00:09:02,000
No one's going
to save you, Riona.

149
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:04,541
[chain saw revving]

150
00:09:04,625 --> 00:09:06,333
[NOBUAKI]
Stop it!

151
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:09,000
[RIONA]
Nobuaki!

152
00:09:09,083 --> 00:09:13,500
-Why'd you do this to Ryou?
-It's our new order.

153
00:09:13,583 --> 00:09:16,583
We're supposed to cut our bodies
to pieces and make a doll.

154
00:09:16,666 --> 00:09:18,000
Catch up, please.

155
00:09:18,083 --> 00:09:20,916
The kid actually
did it to himself.

156
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:24,375
Ryou did this before we could
even talk about it?

157
00:09:24,458 --> 00:09:26,250
[RIONA]
He wanted to.

158
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:30,625
He said he was going to become
stronger, like Teruaki.

159
00:09:30,708 --> 00:09:33,625
He wanted to be more like you.

160
00:09:35,625 --> 00:09:38,541
[NOBUAKI] But you already
were strong, Ryou.

161
00:09:38,625 --> 00:09:41,208
You were so small,
but you ran all this way,

162
00:09:41,291 --> 00:09:43,125
up a whole mountain.

163
00:09:43,208 --> 00:09:44,625
You were exhausted,

164
00:09:44,708 --> 00:09:47,375
but you kept encouraging
everyone to keep going.

165
00:09:47,458 --> 00:09:49,708
You're far more of a man
than I am.

166
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:54,458
You were scared, weren't you?
I know.

167
00:09:54,541 --> 00:09:57,250
But you hung in there.

168
00:09:57,333 --> 00:09:59,583
Well, what happens now?

169
00:09:59,666 --> 00:10:02,500
Do we dig graves
or just continue?

170
00:10:13,708 --> 00:10:15,875
We're supposed to cut up
our own bodies?

171
00:10:15,958 --> 00:10:17,958
Why would he give us
such a sick order?

172
00:10:18,041 --> 00:10:20,875
What does it matter to him
if we make a human doll?

173
00:10:20,958 --> 00:10:23,666
Who cares why he wants us
to do anything?

174
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:26,208
All that matters is
we're going to do it.

175
00:10:26,291 --> 00:10:29,416
[NOBUAKI] We can't keep
following these insane demands!

176
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:32,125
There's barely any of us
left as it is.

177
00:10:32,208 --> 00:10:34,708
Okay, you have to help me think.

178
00:10:34,791 --> 00:10:38,250
Come on. There has to be
some way to survive this.

179
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:40,958
All of us. Isn't there anything
we can do to stop him?

180
00:10:41,041 --> 00:10:42,375
What don't you get?

181
00:10:42,458 --> 00:10:44,875
There's no stopping him,
so suck it up!

182
00:10:46,208 --> 00:10:47,708
Wait.

183
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:52,583
Before you got here, you were
plotting something together.

184
00:10:52,666 --> 00:10:55,000
What were you and Riona
talking about?

185
00:10:55,083 --> 00:10:57,041
What are you planning?

186
00:10:58,666 --> 00:11:00,583
Nobuaki,

187
00:11:00,666 --> 00:11:03,708
maybe we should
work together with her.

188
00:11:03,791 --> 00:11:06,291
She might know something.

189
00:11:06,375 --> 00:11:08,875
We have a few clues
as to how the game works.

190
00:11:11,875 --> 00:11:14,625
Everyone who dies gets
a one-syllable text

191
00:11:14,708 --> 00:11:16,166
sent to their phone.

192
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:18,375
We collected these.

193
00:11:18,458 --> 00:11:22,041
So, do you have any idea
what they could mean?

194
00:11:22,125 --> 00:11:24,416
How 'bout that.
I'm actually impressed.

195
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:27,416
I didn't think you idiots
had noticed anything.

196
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:33,875
I caught on to the same thing

197
00:11:33,958 --> 00:11:36,250
when I played the game
at my last high school.

198
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:39,250
I've been collecting them
since the first order this time.

199
00:11:39,333 --> 00:11:41,333
So far, I haven't been able
to spell out anything

200
00:11:41,416 --> 00:11:43,125
that makes sense.

201
00:11:43,208 --> 00:11:46,416
Hey, maybe if we put the letters
we collected together with hers,

202
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:48,375
they'll form
some kind of sentence.

203
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:51,000
Yeah.
It's like just Ria was saying.

204
00:11:51,083 --> 00:11:53,541
The King's Game is
basically a type of virus

205
00:11:53,625 --> 00:11:56,208
that originated in Yonaki
Village a long time ago.

206
00:11:57,208 --> 00:11:58,958
Yonaki Village.

207
00:12:00,625 --> 00:12:03,500
[NOBUAKI] At some point,
it moved onto the Internet.

208
00:12:03,583 --> 00:12:05,375
Now it exists online.

209
00:12:05,458 --> 00:12:09,166
It's like some kind of mutated
computer virus or something.

210
00:12:09,250 --> 00:12:11,458
That's what's to blame
for these orders.

211
00:12:12,458 --> 00:12:14,125
Let's put our heads together.

212
00:12:14,208 --> 00:12:18,000
If we're lucky, we'll finally
figure out how to beat the game.

213
00:12:18,083 --> 00:12:20,958
Well, this Ria girl's theories
sound ridiculous.

214
00:12:21,041 --> 00:12:23,416
I'm not sure I believe
any of that nonsense.

215
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:25,000
If you think we're stupid,

216
00:12:25,083 --> 00:12:26,916
then why have you been
collecting all these texts too?

217
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,625
They're the only lead we've got.

218
00:12:28,708 --> 00:12:31,041
The only clue we have
to unlocking the secrets

219
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:33,958
of this damn game.
You must think so too.

220
00:12:34,041 --> 00:12:36,583
Otherwise you wouldn't have gone
out of your way to find them.

221
00:12:36,666 --> 00:12:39,208
I didn't do it to end the game
or try to save anybody

222
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:42,625
or to beat the King,
whatever the hell that means.

223
00:12:42,708 --> 00:12:44,791
I just wanted as much
information as possible

224
00:12:44,875 --> 00:12:46,541
that might help me survive.

225
00:12:46,625 --> 00:12:48,666
Plain and simple. That's it.

226
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:50,625
You're serious.

227
00:12:51,625 --> 00:12:53,666
[NATSUKO]
Give me that.

228
00:12:59,333 --> 00:13:01,666
-Look.
-Oh, crap.

229
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:04,625
That has to be it.
That means...

230
00:13:10,833 --> 00:13:13,791
This can't be right. No way.

231
00:13:15,625 --> 00:13:18,916
So basically, none of us
can keep on living

232
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,000
if we really want
to end the game.

233
00:13:22,291 --> 00:13:24,416
The King's Game virus
lives in the bodies

234
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:26,708
of everyone
who's had to play before.

235
00:13:26,791 --> 00:13:29,750
It keeps on spreading
through whoever won.

236
00:13:29,833 --> 00:13:33,333
If you survive, it could pass
from you to others,

237
00:13:33,416 --> 00:13:37,250
and the game will continue
until humanity is wiped out.

238
00:13:37,333 --> 00:13:41,500
Every person on Earth,
killed by a single plague.

239
00:13:41,583 --> 00:13:43,666
In order for us
to end this game,

240
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:46,750
not a single participant
can live when it's over.

241
00:13:48,041 --> 00:13:50,750
If we want to save
every person in the world,

242
00:13:50,833 --> 00:13:53,458
we're all going to have
to die tonight.

243
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:55,750
It's not fair, at all.

244
00:13:55,833 --> 00:13:58,916
We used to be ordinary kids:

245
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:03,541
going to school, getting excited
over sports and new students.

246
00:14:03,625 --> 00:14:05,833
Everything was normal.

247
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:09,958
And now the world
is in our hands?

248
00:14:10,041 --> 00:14:11,750
It's insanity.

249
00:14:12,708 --> 00:14:16,916
[NATSUKO laughing]

250
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,416
So what if everyone dies?

251
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:22,125
There's only one person
I care about.

252
00:14:22,208 --> 00:14:24,708
I bet you're thinking about
trying to be some kind of savior

253
00:14:24,791 --> 00:14:27,750
by sacrificing yourself
to save all of mankind.

254
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:30,333
Always thinking
you can fix everything.

255
00:14:30,416 --> 00:14:31,958
I'm so tired of it.

256
00:14:32,041 --> 00:14:33,416
If we're all going
to die anyway,

257
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:35,833
I'll do you a favor
and kill you myself!

258
00:14:38,291 --> 00:14:40,041
What are you doing?

259
00:14:45,791 --> 00:14:49,333
I'm going to survive this.
I'm not gonna give up yet.

260
00:14:50,875 --> 00:14:52,875
Both of us survived our games,

261
00:14:52,958 --> 00:14:55,958
but that's obviously the only
thing we have in common.

262
00:14:56,041 --> 00:14:59,208
Weren't you changed by all the
horrors you had to go through?

263
00:14:59,291 --> 00:15:00,750
Didn't you feel anything

264
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:02,583
watching your friends
die terrible,

265
00:15:02,666 --> 00:15:06,208
painful deaths after suffering
at the hands of this bastard?

266
00:15:06,291 --> 00:15:09,458
Didn't you learn anything
when the person you loved died?

267
00:15:09,541 --> 00:15:12,500
It made me realize
what my duty really was.

268
00:15:12,583 --> 00:15:14,208
To quickly end the pain

269
00:15:14,291 --> 00:15:16,541
and suffering the others
were going through.

270
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:20,708
Someone has to be the bad guy
in the King's Game.

271
00:15:20,791 --> 00:15:24,333
Someone has to push everyone
to the extreme. You see?

272
00:15:24,416 --> 00:15:26,583
That's the part I played.

273
00:15:30,416 --> 00:15:32,458
You're delusional.

274
00:15:46,541 --> 00:15:48,500
But you, I can't forgive you

275
00:15:48,583 --> 00:15:50,208
for filling them
with your false hope,

276
00:15:50,291 --> 00:15:53,458
saying everything
would be okay in the end.

277
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:59,500
I don't care
if everyone else hates me.

278
00:15:59,583 --> 00:16:02,208
At least I'm not
a liar like you.

279
00:16:02,291 --> 00:16:03,583
That's even worse!

280
00:16:03,666 --> 00:16:06,541
-[chain saw buzzing]
-[screaming]

281
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:12,125
[RIONA]
I won't let you kill Nobuaki!

282
00:16:12,208 --> 00:16:14,041
He means too much to me.

283
00:16:14,125 --> 00:16:15,541
He got us this far!

284
00:16:15,625 --> 00:16:17,666
[chain saw stops]

285
00:16:19,958 --> 00:16:22,000
[gasps, groans]

286
00:16:29,916 --> 00:16:32,208
Was I wrong to try
and give everyone hope?

287
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:34,541
No, you can't listen to her.

288
00:16:34,625 --> 00:16:38,125
I don't know.
She made sense.

289
00:16:41,958 --> 00:16:45,833
Nobuaki,
I want you to look at me.

290
00:16:45,916 --> 00:16:49,708
-I'm looking.
-I'm here only because of you.

291
00:16:49,791 --> 00:16:51,625
You're why I'm alive now.

292
00:16:53,166 --> 00:16:55,208
You did the right thing.

293
00:16:55,291 --> 00:16:57,666
Otherwise, I'd be dead
on the side of the road.

294
00:16:58,875 --> 00:17:01,583
You know, I'd do it again
in a heartbeat.

295
00:17:02,541 --> 00:17:04,875
[RIONA]
Hey, before all this happened,

296
00:17:04,958 --> 00:17:07,166
how long did you think
you'd live?

297
00:17:08,666 --> 00:17:10,625
It doesn't have to be that long.

298
00:17:11,916 --> 00:17:14,250
Why?

299
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:16,208
Because all I want is

300
00:17:16,291 --> 00:17:19,500
to be able to spend
a little of that time with you.

301
00:17:19,583 --> 00:17:22,458
I love you!
I just wish I'd known sooner!

302
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:24,541
-[chain saw buzzing]
-Aah!

303
00:17:28,125 --> 00:17:30,333
You're coming with me.

304
00:17:30,416 --> 00:17:32,166
[RIONA]
No!

305
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:38,333
If you love a person,

306
00:17:38,416 --> 00:17:40,875
it's better to end their life
with your own two hands...

307
00:17:40,958 --> 00:17:43,000
♪

308
00:17:43,083 --> 00:17:45,208
...than to let
someone else do it.

309
00:17:46,250 --> 00:17:49,833
I won't give him to you.
He's mine.

310
00:17:53,708 --> 00:17:55,708
♪

311
00:18:02,166 --> 00:18:07,000
-Natsuko...
-It's okay, my Nobu.

312
00:18:11,375 --> 00:18:14,916
-Nobuaki!
-Riona...

313
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:18,375
Just focus on me,
and I can stop the bleeding.

314
00:18:18,458 --> 00:18:22,208
It's over.
She cut me way too deep.

315
00:18:22,291 --> 00:18:26,166
No. Don't say that.
There has to be a way!

316
00:18:26,250 --> 00:18:27,458
[RIONA sobbing]

317
00:18:27,541 --> 00:18:30,208
[NOBUAKI]
Make me a promise.

318
00:18:30,291 --> 00:18:32,458
Survive this.

319
00:18:32,541 --> 00:18:35,208
Will you do that
one thing for me?

320
00:18:35,291 --> 00:18:36,416
But I can't.

321
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:38,958
I'm not strong enough
to keep going.

322
00:18:39,041 --> 00:18:41,291
So you're not allowed
to die yet.

323
00:18:41,375 --> 00:18:46,541
You hear me?
Don't go, Nobuaki. Nobuaki?

324
00:18:48,541 --> 00:18:49,583
No.

325
00:18:55,416 --> 00:18:56,666
[sobs]

326
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:58,500
Nobuaki!

327
00:19:03,083 --> 00:19:05,125
♪

328
00:19:15,041 --> 00:19:18,708
Nobuaki, there you are.

329
00:19:21,166 --> 00:19:24,666
Chiemi, it's you!

330
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,708
You're all here.

331
00:19:57,791 --> 00:19:59,833
♪

332
00:20:34,875 --> 00:20:36,916
I know this seems weird.

333
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:40,958
But it is kind of romantic,
us alone on the beach?

334
00:20:44,125 --> 00:20:46,375
Sorry for dragging you
all the way out here.

335
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:54,958
You're freezing.

336
00:20:56,416 --> 00:20:59,041
I warmed you up
this way last time.

337
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:05,541
Come on.
At least open your eyes.

338
00:21:05,625 --> 00:21:08,083
I'm ordering you to kiss me.

339
00:21:10,041 --> 00:21:11,541
[RIONA sobbing]

340
00:21:12,583 --> 00:21:15,000
You can't just lay there
and ignore me.

341
00:21:15,083 --> 00:21:17,000
I'm begging you to wake up!

342
00:21:36,208 --> 00:21:38,250
♪

343
00:23:27,541 --> 00:23:29,458
-[GIRL 1] Good morning!
-[GIRL 2] Hi!

344
00:23:29,541 --> 00:23:31,583
[students chattering]

345
00:23:35,541 --> 00:23:39,541
[chiming]

346
00:23:39,625 --> 00:23:42,291
What the hell?
A game?

